<DIV type=1>

<HEAD weight="bold" >
Does Terra-Cortril Nystatin Cream cause undesirable
</HEAD>


</DIV>
<DIV type=1>

<HEAD weight="bold" >
effects?
</HEAD>


<BLOCK>
Undesirable effects may occur occasionally. The following may be a problem in the area that the cream is used:
</BLOCK>


<LIST type="bulleted">

<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
burning
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
itching
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
dryness
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
skin rash or allergic reaction
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
acne
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
thinning of the skin
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
spread or worsening of infection
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
swelling of the hair-roots in the skin (folliculitis)
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
excessive growth of hair on the skin (hypertrichosis)
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
white patches on the skin (hypopigmentation)
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>

</LIST>



<BLOCK>
These effects should disappear if you stop using Terra-Cortril Nystatin Cream. If the discomfort continues tell your doctor or pharmacist Check with your doctor or pharmacist immediately if any of the following occur:
</BLOCK>


<LIST type="bulleted">

<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
wheeziness, difficulty breathing or tightness in the chest
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
swelling of eyelids, face or lips
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>


<ITEM>

<BLOCK>
skin lumps or itchy red spots
</BLOCK>

</ITEM>

</LIST>



<BLOCK>
If the patient becomes unwell or has any discomfort whilst using the cream, tell your doctor or pharmacist.
</BLOCK>

